modules.description: Handles compression and decompression of Git object packs, enabling efficient storage and retrieval of commits, trees, blobs, and tags. Operates on binary data structures representing packed objects and their indices. Used to optimize network transfer during repository cloning and reduce disk usage in local repositories.

Provides functions for configuring and verifying data streams, generating deltas, and creating pack files with custom compression and indexing. Operates on types like `Carton.Value.t`, `Carton.Uid.t`, and `Cartonnage.Entry.t` to manage data integrity and storage. Used to verify content from a stream, generate incremental updates, and build indexed storage structures for efficient data retrieval.
